{
  "text": "The strategy proposed by van Dijk et al. [CITATION_1] , which combines temocillin <11 mm and the Rosco confirmatory test with regard to isolates selected on meropenem MIC \u22650.5 mg/L (i.e. estimated inhibition zone diameter <25 mm) [CITATION_2] , displayed a Se of 55.8% and a Sp of 90.6% in our collection of isolates (Table 2) . It has to be noted that 73.9% of the isolates of our study, including 20 of the 52 CPE, would not have been tested because they displayed a meropenem inhibition zone diameter \u226525 mm, which is used as first screening criteria by the authors (Additional file 1: Figure S1 ).",
